'''Cannibalism''' was the term for when a [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Species/Legends|species]], sometimes due to food shortages or famine, ate members of their own kind. The term was also used to describe individuals or species who consumed members of other sentient species.

==Cannibalism in the galaxy==
The [[Rakata/Legends|Rakatan]] individual known as [[The One]] forced many species to revert to this practice. The [[Insectoid/Legends|insectoid]] [[Colicoid/Legends|Colicoids]] were known cannibals, eating off-worlders who landed on their [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] and sometimes capturing vessels which passed too close. The [[Reptile/Legends|reptilian]] [[Marit]]s were traditionally cannibals, as well, though the Marits' only ate those who had already [[Death/Legends|died]], and did so as a means of disposing of the bodies in a way they deemed beneficial to the living.

Certain [[Hutt/Legends|Hutts]] were known to eat their enemies, [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba Desilijic Tiure]] among them.

The [[Zanibar]] under the employ of [[Grappa (Hutt)|Grappa the Hutt]] carried out ritualistic sacrifices and consumption of other sentients.<ref name="CEII2">[[Crimson Empire II: Council of Blood 2|''Crimson Empire II: Council of Blood'' 2]]</ref>

[[Dezono Qua]], a [[Human/Legends|Human]] who lived during the rise of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], was a known cannibal; he purchased [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]] at market and had his [[Droid/Legends|droid]] cook them.

[[Bossk/Legends|Bossk]], a [[Trandoshan/Legends|Trandoshan]] [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]], had cannibalistic tendencies, as he, in addition to savoring Zanibar and [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiees]],<ref name="BHC">''[[The Bounty Hunter Code: From the Files of Boba Fett]]''</ref> had devoured his siblings before they could hatch, as well as his own [[Cradossk/Legends|father]] later in life.<ref name="TMA">''[[The Mandalorian Armor]]''</ref>

[[The Children]] were a tribe formed from the descendants of a [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]] survey team stranded on [[Dagobah/Legends|Dagobah]]. As their food supplies ran out, the members of the survey team were forced to resort to cannibalism to feed their children, a practice that continued as the survey team died off and the children aged. By [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]], a group of the Children that had pursued [[Zak Arranda/Legends|Zak Arranda]] to Dagobah's [[Cave of Evil/Legends|Cave of Evil]] were shown visions of the horror and revulsion the survey team had experienced as they fed their children human flesh. The smuggler [[Platt Okeefe/Legends|Platt Okeefe]] agreed to transfer the Children offworld.<ref name="Hunger">[[Galaxy of Fear: The Hunger|''Galaxy of Fear: The Hunger'']]</ref>

Certain Human cannibals were known to roam throughout the [[City/Legends|cities]] and wilderness of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]].<ref name="SWG">{{GalaxiesAED}}</ref>

